com.i2group.apollo.externaldata.subsetexplorationservice
Interface IExternalDataSubsetExplorationService

public interface IExternalDataSubsetExplorationService

A set of methods for performing searches of various kinds against a data subset that has been created from an external data provider.

Since:
3.1

Method Detail

initialize

ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier initialize(ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier subsetIdentifier)
                                        throws InvalidArgumentException,
                                               ValidationException,
                                               ExternalDataSourceException
Initializes the service so that it is ready to receive search requests for the external data subset with the specified ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier. Typically, initialization involves the creation of an item cache and indexes from the data subset.

Note: If this method is not called before a search request is made, the search request performs initialization before the search takes place.

Parameters:
subsetIdentifier - An ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier that identifies the external data subset with which to initialize the service.
Returns:
An ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier that contains updated information about the external data subset.
Throws:
InvalidArgumentException - If the specified ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier is not valid.
ValidationException - If a general validation error occurs.
ExternalDataSourceException - If an error occurs during processing of the external data subset.

dumbbellSearch

SearchSummary dumbbellSearch(ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier subsetIdentifier,
                             SearchNode fromEntity,
                             SearchNode link,
                             SearchNode toEntity)
                             throws InvalidArgumentException,
                                    ValidationException,
                                    ExternalDataSourceException,
                                    CacheTimeoutException,
                                    CacheInaccessibleException,
                                    StringArgumentTooLongException
Searches the external data subset with the specified ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier for dumbbells meeting a range of criteria, returning a SearchSummary. Dumbbells can be included in or excluded from the SearchSummary depending on how they match the specified SearchNodes, which must be populated following the same rules as the arguments to search.

Items appear (or do not appear) in the SearchSummary according to the same security requirements as those for search.

Parameters:
subsetIdentifier - An ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier that identifies the external data subset to be searched.
fromEntity - A SearchNode containing criteria that an Entity at the "from" end of a dumbbell must match.
link - A SearchNode containing criteria that the Link in a dumbbell must match.
toEntity - A SearchNode containing criteria that an Entity at the "to" end of a dumbbell must match.
Returns:
See above.
Throws:
InvalidArgumentException - If any of the arguments are not valid.
ValidationException - If a general validation error occurs.
ExternalDataSourceException - If an error occurs during processing of the external data subset.
CacheTimeoutException - If the search is not possible due to a timeout of the item cache.
CacheInaccessibleException - If the search is not possible due to the item cache being inaccessible to the current user.
StringArgumentTooLongException - If a String in any of the arguments is too long.

expand

ExternalDataResults expand(List<ProvenanceGroup> provenanceGroups,
                           boolean includeRetrievalBlockMap,
                           int maxNumberOfLinks,
                           boolean shouldThrowIfTooManyLinks)
                           throws InvalidArgumentException,
                                  TooManyItemsException,
                                  TooManySeedsException,
                                  ExternalDataSourceException
Gets an ExternalDataResults that contains Links from an external data subset (together with their associated ends), connected to Entitys that are identified through the provenance information in the specified ProvenanceGroups.

Where possible, all the Links are returned for each of the identified Entitys. If both ends of a Link are identified through the ProvenanceGroups, then the Link is returned twice (once for each end).

A Link is only returned if it meets the security requirements for it to appear in the SearchSummary after a call to search.

Parameters:
provenanceGroups - The ProvenanceGroups that contain the information that identifies the Entitys to be expanded in the external data subset.
includeRetrievalBlockMap - true if the ItemGroups in the returned ExternalDataResults should contain information that connects the retrieved Items to the RetrievalBlocks that caused them to be retrieved; false otherwise.
maxNumberOfLinks - The maximum number of Links to be returned in the ExternalDataResults.
shouldThrowIfTooManyLinks - true to throw an exception (and return no results) when the number of Links connected to the identified Entitys exceeds maxNumberOfLinks; false to throw no exception and return up to maxNumberOfLinks results. If maxNumberOfLinks is not exceeded, this parameter has no effect.
Returns:
See above. If maxNumberOfLinks is exceeded, the order and contents of the results are not defined.
Throws:
InvalidArgumentException - If any of the arguments are not valid.
TooManyItemsException - If more Items will be returned than the limit in maxNumberOfLinks, and shouldThrowIfTooManyLinks is true.
TooManySeedsException - If the specified ProvenanceGroups resolve to too many seed Entitys.
ExternalDataSourceException - If an error occurs during processing of the external data subset.

retrieve

SearchResults retrieve(String searchToken,
                       DumbbellPart dumbbellPart,
                       ItemTypeIdList itemTypeIds,
                       FilterInfoList filterInfos,
                       SortInfo sortInfo,
                       int maxResultCount,
                       PageInfo pageInfo)
                       throws InvalidArgumentException,
                              ValidationException,
                              ExternalDataSourceException,
                              CacheTimeoutException,
                              CacheInaccessibleException,
                              StringArgumentTooLongException
Retrieves SearchResults created by a previous call to search or dumbbellSearch, allowing sorting and additional filtering to be carried out. Sorting and filtering depend on whether Items:
  • Have an ItemType with a specified identifier.
  • Contain Propertys with specified (ranges of) values.
  • Occupy a particular position within a dumbbell.
See the search documentation for the rules that govern whether an Item appears in the SearchResults at all. The following rules then determine how it appears.

An Item is returned as an ItemPlaceholder when:

  • The user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.READ_CLOAKED on the Item.
  • The Item is a deleted end Entity of a Link that has been returned.
An Item is returned as an Item when:
  • The Item is not deleted, and the user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.READ_ONLY (or above) on the Item.

When retrieving results from a dumbbellSearch, the following additional rules apply to dumbbells with deleted parts:

  • If DumbbellPart.ALL was specified, then dumbbells with deleted parts are included in the SearchResults, subject to these conditions:
    • Deleted ends are included only if there are no additional constraints (that is, no search terms, filters, or item types are applied).
    • Deleted links are never returned.
  • If DumbbellPart.FROM, DumbbellPart.LINK, or DumbbellPart.TO was specified, then dumbbells with deleted parts are not included in the SearchResults.

The returned SearchResults only contain highlighting information in the CardInfos if the call to search or dumbbellSearch included a search string (or filterInfos that used strings). In the case of dumbbellSearch, highlighting information is only included if DumbbellPart.ALL was specified.

Parameters:
searchToken - A String that identifies the results to retrieve.
dumbbellPart - A DumbbellPart indicating the location in dumbbells that matching Items must occupy. When retrieving results from a search, this must be set to DumbbellPart.NONE. When retrieving results from a dumbbellSearch, this can be set to DumbbellPart.FROM, DumbbellPart.LINK, DumbbellPart.TO, or DumbbellPart.ALL.
itemTypeIds - An ItemTypeIdList containing identifiers for the ItemTypes that matching Items must have, or null to match all Items. The ItemTypeIdList specified must be a subset of the ItemTypeIdList used in the preceding search operation.
filterInfos - A FilterInfoList defining Property and metadata values that matching Items must have, or null to match all Items. This FilterInfoList is additional to the one specified in the preceding call to search or dumbbellSearch. This parameter must be null when itemTypeIds identifies more than one ItemType, or when dumbbellPart is set to DumbbellPart.ALL.
sortInfo - A SortInfo determining how the retrieved Items are to be ordered.
maxResultCount - The maximum number of Items to return to the client, which must not be negative.
pageInfo - A PageInfo indicating which page of results to retrieve.
Returns:
See above.
Throws:
InvalidArgumentException - If any of the arguments are not valid.
ValidationException - If a general validation error occurs.
CacheTimeoutException - If the search results are not available due to a timeout of the item cache.
CacheInaccessibleException - If the search results are not available due to the item cache being inaccessible to the current user.
StringArgumentTooLongException - If a String in any of the arguments is too long.
ExternalDataSourceException

search

SearchSummary search(ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier subsetIdentifier,
                     String searchString,
                     SetInfo setInfo,
                     ItemTypeIdList itemTypeIds,
                     FilterInfoList filterInfos)
                     throws InvalidArgumentException,
                            ValidationException,
                            SetSizeExceededException,
                            ExternalDataSourceException,
                            CacheTimeoutException,
                            CacheInaccessibleException,
                            StringArgumentTooLongException
Searches the specified external data subset for Items meeting a range of criteria, returning a SearchSummary. Items can be included in or excluded from the SearchSummary depending on whether they:
  • Contain a specified String.
  • Appear in a set owned by a specified Item.
  • Have an ItemType with a specified identifier.
  • Contain Propertys or metadata with specified (ranges of) values.

However, an Item that would otherwise appear in the SearchSummary is not included when:

  • The user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.READ_CLOAKED on a set owner.
  • The user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.NONE on the Item.
  • The Item is a Link with an end Entity on which the user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.NONE.
  • The Item is deleted.

Otherwise, an Item is included in the SearchSummary when:

  • The Item is not deleted, and the user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.READ_CLOAKED (or above) on it.
  • The Item is a Link with a deleted end.

Parameters:
subsetIdentifier - An ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier that identifies the external data subset to be searched.
searchString - A String that contains some text that matching Items must contain, or null to match all Items.
setInfo - A SetInfo that specifies the Item that owns the set that matching Items must be in, or null to match all Items.
itemTypeIds - An ItemTypeIdList that contains the identifiers for the ItemTypes that matching Items must have, or null to match all Items.
filterInfos - A FilterInfoList that defines Property and metadata values that matching Items must have, or null to match all Items. This parameter must be null when itemTypeIds identifies more than one ItemType.
Returns:
See above, or null if any set owner specified by SetInfo:
  • Does not own a set.
  • Has been deleted.
  • Does not exist.
  • Has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.NONE for the current user.
Throws:
InvalidArgumentException - If any of the arguments are not valid.
ValidationException - If a general validation error occurs.
SetSizeExceededException - If a set is too large to be searched.
ExternalDataSourceException - If an error occurs during processing of the external data subset.
CacheTimeoutException - If the search is not possible due to a timeout of the item cache.
CacheInaccessibleException - If the search is not possible due to the item cache being inaccessible to the current user.
StringArgumentTooLongException - If a String in any of the arguments is too long.

networkSearch

SearchSummary networkSearch(ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier subsetIdentifier,
                            NetworkSearchNodeList networkSearchCriteria)
                            throws NodeUsesTooLargeSetException,
                                   NodeMatchesTooManyItemsException,
                                   NetworkSearchMatchesTooManyNetworksException,
                                   ExternalDataSourceException,
                                   InvalidArgumentException,
                                   NetworkSearchValidationException,
                                   ValidationException,
                                   CacheTimeoutException,
                                   CacheInaccessibleException
Searches the specified external data subset for groups of Items that together meet the assembled criteria of the nodes in a network, returning a SearchSummary.

Groups of Items are included in or excluded from the SearchSummary depending on whether individual Items match the specified NetworkSearchNodes. The SearchNodes in NetworkSearchNodes must be populated following the same rules as the arguments to search.

Groups of Items appear (or do not appear) in the SearchSummary according to the same security requirements as those for search, which are applied to the individual Items in the group.

Parameters:
subsetIdentifier - An ExternalDataSubsetIdentifier that identifies the external data subset to be searched.
networkSearchCriteria - A NetworkSearchNodeList that contains NetworkSearchNodes that define the criteria and structure that Items must match.
Returns:
See above.
Throws:
NodeUsesTooLargeSetException - If the search cannot be processed because one of the nodes matches a set that contains too many items.
NodeMatchesTooManyItemsException - If the search cannot be processed because one of the nodes matches more items than the server allows.
NetworkSearchMatchesTooManyNetworksException - If the search cannot be processed because it matches more networks than the server allows.
ExternalDataSourceException - If an error occurs during processing of the external data subset.
InvalidArgumentException - If any of the arguments are not valid.
NetworkSearchValidationException - If one of the following network structure rules is broken, or if any other network search validation error occurs:
  • A network must contain at least one NetworkSearchNode.
  • Every NetworkSearchNode must be connected to at least one other NetworkSearchNode, unless there is only one EntityNetworkSearchNode in the network.
  • Every LinkNetworkSearchNode must be connected to two EntityNetworkSearchNodes.
  • NetworkSearchNode identifiers must be unique within the network.
ValidationException - If a general validation error occurs.
CacheTimeoutException - If the search is not possible due to a timeout of the item cache.
CacheInaccessibleException - If the search is not possible due to the item cache being inaccessible to the current user.

networkRetrieve

SearchResults networkRetrieve(String searchToken,
                              ItemTypeIdList itemTypeIds,
                              FilterInfoList filterInfos,
                              SortInfo sortInfo,
                              int maxResultCount,
                              PageInfo pageInfo)
                              throws NodeUsesTooLargeSetException,
                                     NodeMatchesTooManyItemsException,
                                     NetworkSearchMatchesTooManyNetworksException,
                                     ExternalDataSourceException,
                                     InvalidArgumentException,
                                     ValidationException,
                                     CacheTimeoutException,
                                     CacheInaccessibleException,
                                     StringArgumentTooLongException
Retrieves SearchResults created by a previous call to networkSearch, allowing sorting and additional filtering to be carried out. Sorting and filtering depend on whether Items:
  • Have an ItemType with a specified identifier.
  • Contain Propertys with specified (ranges of) values.
See the search documentation for the rules that govern whether an Item appears in the SearchResults at all. The following rules then determine how it appears.

An Item is returned as an ItemPlaceholder when:

  • The user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.READ_CLOAKED on the Item.
  • The Item is a deleted end Entity of a Link that has been returned.

An Item is returned as an Item when:

  • The Item is not deleted, and the user has an access level of SecurityAccessLevel.READ_ONLY (or above) on the Item.

The returned SearchResults do not contain highlighting information in the CardInfos.

Parameters:
searchToken - A String that identifies the results to retrieve.
itemTypeIds - An ItemTypeIdList containing identifiers for the ItemTypes that matching Items must have. This ItemTypeIdList must contain a subset of the identifiers involved in the call to networkSearch, or null to match all legal ItemTypes.
filterInfos - A FilterInfoList defining Property and metadata values that matching Items must have, or null to match all Items. This parameter must be null when itemTypeIds identifies more than one ItemType.
sortInfo - A SortInfo determining how the retrieved Items are to be ordered.
maxResultCount - The maximum number of Items to return to the client, which must not be negative.
pageInfo - A PageInfo indicating which page of results to retrieve.
Returns:
See above.
Throws:
NodeUsesTooLargeSetException - If the search cannot be processed because one of the nodes matches a set that contains too many items.
NodeMatchesTooManyItemsException - If the search cannot be processed because one of the nodes matches more items than the server allows.
InvalidArgumentException - If any of the arguments are not valid.
ExternalDataSourceException - If an error occurs during processing of the external data subset.
StringArgumentTooLongException - If a String in any of the arguments is too long.
ValidationException - If a general validation error occurs.
CacheTimeoutException - If the search results are not available due to a timeout of the item cache.
CacheInaccessibleException - If the search results are not available due to the item cache being inaccessible to the current user.
NetworkSearchMatchesTooManyNetworksException - If the search cannot be processed because it matches more networks than the server allows.
StringArgumentTooLongException - If a String in any of the arguments is too long.
